snippet.textDisplay:
Maguire was a red card 100%. The other two decisions in my opinion are 100% correct.

Offside is offside, there’s no two ways about it, simple, right decision.

As for the Azpilicueta foul, contact happens in the box constantly and Fred merely brushes him as opposed to pushing him as people are claiming was the case. That is not a foul. If a penalty was given for that and Williams wasn’t in the equation we would all be sitting here debating how it isn’t a penalty and how the slightest of contact in a box now constitutes as a penalty is wrong.

Truth of the matter is yes Azpilicueta naturally would put his hands forward to brace his forward movement but he still forcefully pushed Williams after he has planted his feet and therefor gains an advantage on the ball, a ball that would have been cleared by Williams had he not been thrown to the ground by Azpilicueta. Correct decision for me but everything is subjective.
